# About the Project

The editorjs-toolkit is a monolithic for Editor.js into a single package. The idea is to simplify the installation and configuration process, allowing you to quickly add robust functionalities to your editor with just one file.

This project is an easy-to-use starter kit, designed for quick setup in a local development environment using an extension like VS Code's Live Server.

# Getting Started

There's no need for complex installations. To get started with the editorjs-toolkit:

1. Clone this repository to your machine.

1. Open the project folder in VS Code.

1. Open the index.html file and click Go Live on the bottom bar to start the Live Server.

That's it! You can now use the editor with all the integrated plugins.

# Contributing

Contributions are very welcome! If you have an idea for a new plugin, found a bug, or want to suggest improvements, feel free to open an issue.